cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with identifying influential nodes in a network, which is a common problem in social and information networks. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The proposed method can be applied to software engineering networks such as dependency networks or call graphs. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm to estimate the shell-index of a node, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The hill-climbing based approach proposed in the paper can be applied to control systems to optimize the performance of a system. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with network analysis and proposes a method to estimate the rank of a node, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture.
